# Project Overview: Arthur Geron's Personal Website

## Description
Arthur Geron's personal website is a modern, well-animated portfolio designed to showcase his skills and experience as a software engineer, focusing on his expertise in Web3, React development, and Fuel Network contributions.

## Goals
- Create a professional, visually appealing portfolio website
- Highlight technical skills with an emphasis on Web3 & React
- Showcase projects and experience
- Implement smooth animations and interactive elements
- Provide easy contact options for potential opportunities

## Target Persona: Arthur Geron
Arthur Geron is a software engineer specializing in:
- Web3 development & blockchain technologies
- React and React Native development
- Web3 contributor
- ESLint plugin development (notably ESLint Plugin for React useMemo)
- Frontend architecture and performance optimization

## Key Features
- Responsive design optimized for all device sizes
- Animated particle background on the hero section
- Dark/light theme toggle based on user preference
- Interactive project cards
- Smooth page transitions and scroll animations
- Social links to GitHub and other platforms
- Contact form for direct communication

## Implementation
The site is built using modern web technologies with a focus on performance and clean design:
- SolidJS for UI rendering and reactivity
- TailwindCSS with DaisyUI for styling
- GSAP and Motion One for animations
- Rspack for efficient bundling
- TypeScript for type safety 
- Almost never use comments, the code should speak for itself.